  "root_text": {
    "iti15:0.1": "Itivuttaka 15 ",
    "iti15:0.2": "Ekakanipāta ",
    "iti15:0.3": "Dutiyavagga ",
    "iti15:0.4": "Taṇhāsaṁyojanasutta ",
    "iti15:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti15:2.1": "“Nāhaṁ, bhikkhave, aññaṁ ekasaṁyojanampi samanupassāmi yena saṁyojanena saṁyuttā sattā dīgharattaṁ sandhāvanti saṁsaranti yathayidaṁ, bhikkhave, taṇhāsaṁyojanaṁ. ",
    "iti15:2.2": "Taṇhāsaṁyojanena hi, bhikkhave, saṁyuttā sattā dīgharattaṁ sandhāvanti saṁsarantī”ti. ",
    "iti15:2.3": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti15:2.4": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti15:3.1": "“Taṇhādutiyo puriso, ",
    "iti15:3.2": "dīghamaddhāna saṁsaraṁ; ",
    "iti15:3.3": "Itthabhāvaññathābhāvaṁ, ",
    "iti15:3.4": "saṁsāraṁ nātivattati. ",
    "iti15:4.1": "Etamādīnavaṁ ñatvā, ",
    "iti15:4.2": "Taṇhaṁ dukkhassa sambhavaṁ; ",
    "iti15:4.3": "Vītataṇho anādāno, ",
    "iti15:4.4": "Sato bhikkhu paribbaje”ti. ",
    "iti15:5.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti15:5.2": "Pañcamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti15:0.1": "So It Was Said 15 ",
    "iti15:0.2": "The Book of the Ones ",
    "iti15:0.3": "Chapter Two ",
    "iti15:0.4": "The Fetter of Craving ",
    "iti15:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti15:2.1": "“Mendicants, I do not see a single fetter, fettered by which people wander and transmigrate for a long time like the fetter of craving. ",
    "iti15:2.2": "Fettered by craving, people wander and transmigrate for a long time.” ",
    "iti15:2.3": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti15:2.4": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti15:3.1": "“Craving is a person’s partner ",
    "iti15:3.2": "as they transmigrate on this long journey. ",
    "iti15:3.3": "They go from this state to another, ",
    "iti15:3.4": "but don’t escape transmigration. ",
    "iti15:4.1": "Knowing this danger, ",
    "iti15:4.2": "that craving is the cause of suffering—",
    "iti15:4.3": "rid of craving, free of grasping, ",
    "iti15:4.4": "a mendicant would wander mindful.” ",
    "iti15:5.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti15:2.1": "yena → yenevaṁ (sya-all); yeneva (pts-vp-pli1) | taṇhāsaṁyojanaṁ → taṇhāsaṁyojanena (?) ",
    "iti15:3.3": "Itthabhāvaññathābhāvaṁ → itthambhāvaññathābhāvaṁ (sya-all) ",
